title: Use the md-5 crate from RustCrypto
Introduce the 'full' feature
body:
Part of the reason why rusty-s3 was created is to have a faster to compile alternative to other s3 clients. Unfortunately adding more actions also meant having to add more dependencies.

This adds the enabled by default `full` feature, which can in the future be split into smaller features without making breaking changes, which makes it possible to disable the more complicated methods and only have to compile the simpler ones. This in turn reduces the number of dependencies

title: Prepare 0.2.0
body: There are still a few issues we'd like to fix. Opening this early just to signal that we're planning for a 0.2.0 release after it.

title: Use dualstack endpoints in doc tests
Bucket::new() returns now a Result instead of Option
Move 'sign_with_time' method to 'S3Action'
body: As per https://github.com/paolobarbolini/rusty-s3/issues/27, this PR moves the the `sign_with_time` to the `S3Action` trait.

title: Bump MSRV to 1.52
body: Caused by the time crate bumping it's MSRV
